Helvetica Family
.pg
One of the most popular typefaces of all times, Helvetica was designed
by Max Miedinger in 1957 for the Hass foundry in Switzerland.
The name is derived from \fIHelvetia\fR, the Swiss name for Switzerland.
Helvetica's range of styles allows a variety of uses, including headlines,
packaging, posters, and short text blocks, such as captions.
.sp
.ft H
.FS Helvetica
.sp
